      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic mesh refinement study with Richardson extrapolation or GCI estimate required for all quantities of interest at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the impeller passage; GCI computed for pressure head (GCI = 1.8%) and flow rate. Hemolysis index GCI was not directly computed; surrogate GCI from wall shear stress used. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must replicate COU operating conditions including fluid properties, boundary conditions, and device geometry at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments used bovine blood at 37°C with hematocrit 33±2%. VAD operating conditions (flow rate, rotational speed) matched across 5 operating points. However, experiments were conducted at atmospheric outlet pressure rather than physiological back-pressure, introducing a boundary condition mismatch for the COU. Achieved level 3 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of model outputs to experimental measurements using appropriate metrics including uncertainty bounds at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index compared at all 5 operating points; relative errors range from 4.4% to 18.2%. Experimental measurement uncertainty (±12% for HI) documented. Model prediction intervals from Monte Carlo sampling are reported in the narrative but are not formally linked as UQ artifacts for all operating points. Achieved level 3 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be the same as or directly traceable to those used in the COU decision at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index (HI) is the primary QoI in both validation and COU. The power-law hemolysis model directly predicts HI as used in the regulatory submission. Minor gap: validation uses whole-pump HI while COU requires regional HI mapping for hotspot identification. Achieved level 4 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must use the same device geometry, blood analog, and operating envelope as the COU at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry which matches COU geometry. Blood analog (bovine blood) differs from human blood used in clinical COU. Operating envelope covers 5 of the 8 COU operating points; 3 high-speed points (>3500 RPM) not validated. Achieved level 3 against required level 5."
    },
