      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification for selection of turbulence model, hemolysis model form, and constitutive relations must be provided with sensitivity analysis at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected without sensitivity study comparing alternative models (e.g., RSM, LES). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) used without comparison to alternative damage accumulation models. Model form uncertainty not quantified. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in model input parameters (viscosity, density, hemolysis model constants) must be propagated through the model at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo sampling performed on hemolysis model constants (alpha, beta) and blood viscosity. However, uncertainty in pump geometry (manufacturing tolerances) and inlet flow profile not included in the Monte Carlo analysis. Partial UQ coverage leaves input uncertainty incompletely characterized. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
